The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, June 30, 2003  Calcutta Column
 
	The footpath around the GPO is inaccessible to pedestrians,  as hawkers have occupied most of it. The state government  was very active in evicting hawkers from Gariahat and Rashbehari  Avenue, then why did it leave out BBD Bag? Clearing the  kerbs is a better move than imposing a fine on jaywalkers.  
	T.R. Anand, Budge Budge.  
	Several shops in the markets of Purbachal and its adjoining  areas use faulty weighing machines. As a result, customers  are having to pay multiples of the actual rates of essential  commodities. This practice goes unnoticed by the local authorities.  
	 Madhumita Ghosh, Purbachal. 

